webpackJsonp([0xaca7fb325bd4],{413:function(a,e){a.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Blog by Arjun Kava",subtitle:"I am a tireless seeker of knowledge, occasional purveyor of wisdom and also, coincidentally, a deep learning engineer.",copyright:"© All rights reserved.",author:{name:"Arjun Kava",twitter:"arjun_kava"},disqusShortname:"arjun-kava",url:"https://arjun-kava.github.io/"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Volumes/multimedia/Personal-Repositories/arjunkava-blog/src/pages/articles/2018-08-08-we-need-to-go-deeper/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<blockquote>\n<p>“Life is really simple, but we insist on making it complicated.” ― Confucius</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>When I had started to learn about <em>Machine Learning</em>, <em>Deep Learning</em>, and <em>Neural Networks</em>, It was like finding a beam of light in a complete dark hole but you know science black hole is a region in space in which the singularity’s gravitational force is so strong that not even light can escape its pull.</p>\n<p>So I was in completely wrong directions rather than finding light, I need to look ar <em>Singularity’s Gravitational</em>. Then I decided to get into fundamentals.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/meme-deep-d711640323014eebfa68e4a487f0dad5-598e0.jpeg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 570px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 54.56140350877193%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="meme-deep.jpeg"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/meme-deep-d711640323014eebfa68e4a487f0dad5-598e0.jpeg"\n        srcset="/static/meme-deep-d711640323014eebfa68e4a487f0dad5-16eec.jpeg 240w,\n/static/meme-deep-d711640323014eebfa68e4a487f0dad5-ecd97.jpeg 480w,\n/static/meme-deep-d711640323014eebfa68e4a487f0dad5-598e0.jpeg 570w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \nImage Source: <a href="https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/we-need-to-go-deeper">knowyourmeme</a></p>\n<p>Today’s article is all about going deeper into the fancy word called ”<em>Convolutional Neural Network</em>” and here is our roadmap</p>\n<ol>\n<li>How did computer see an image?</li>\n<li>Convolutional Neural Network (CNN)</li>\n<li>Understanding at Deeper Level</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>How did computer see an image?</h3>\n<p>The Image is nothing but three-dimensional array which contains pixel values varied from 0 to 255 as shown below where <strong>rows equal to the width</strong>, <strong>cols equal to height</strong> and <strong>depth is intensity such as RGB, HSV etc</strong>.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/row-major-3D-414f2bf4e305a50d9687ffb116f050d4-8da64.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 799px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 48.81101376720902%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="row-major-3D.png"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/row-major-3D-414f2bf4e305a50d9687ffb116f050d4-8da64.png"\n        srcset="/static/row-major-3D-414f2bf4e305a50d9687ffb116f050d4-c0166.png 240w,\n/static/row-major-3D-414f2bf4e305a50d9687ffb116f050d4-cc06e.png 480w,\n/static/row-major-3D-414f2bf4e305a50d9687ffb116f050d4-8da64.png 799w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 799px) 100vw, 799px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \nImage Source: <a href="https://eli.thegreenplace.net/2015/memory-layout-of-multi-dimensional-arrays">thegreenplace</a></p>\n<p>So for our CPU / GPU, It is a bunch of integers which reflects the intensity of color, at the end of the day everything is just a reflection of light.</p>\n<p>Now you can understand, How does these Instagram filters works!</p>\n<h3>Convolutional Neural Network (CNN)</h3>\n<p>In machine learning, <em>a convolutional neural network (CNN, or ConvNet)</em> is a class of deep, feed-forward artificial neural networks, most commonly applied to analyzing visual imagery. - <em>Wikipedia</em></p>\n<p>I think above defination is perfect but more complex to digest, So here is much simpler. CNN is very similar to Neural Network but it takes images as input and allow us to encode certain properties into the architecture. (if you don’t know neural network read this blog <a href="https://arjun-kava.github.io/posts/prove-simplification-of-neural-network/">Prove Simplification of Artificial Neural Network</a>)</p>\n<p>In more general words, CNN extract features of image and store it as weights which is used to predict for which image stands for. Technically It is structured stack of Neural Network Layers responsible for extracting feature from a images which network has seen to predict possiblities in unseen image.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/cnn-5dbb96f16b91ac0639a42e2dfbd0d901-f9099.jpg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 960px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 33.78486055776892%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="cnn.jpg"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/cnn-5dbb96f16b91ac0639a42e2dfbd0d901-d564d.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/cnn-5dbb96f16b91ac0639a42e2dfbd0d901-865fd.jpg 240w,\n/static/cnn-5dbb96f16b91ac0639a42e2dfbd0d901-d40a0.jpg 480w,\n/static/cnn-5dbb96f16b91ac0639a42e2dfbd0d901-d564d.jpg 960w,\n/static/cnn-5dbb96f16b91ac0639a42e2dfbd0d901-f9099.jpg 1255w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \nImage Source: <a href="https://www.mathworks.com/content/mathworks/www/en/solutions/deep-learning/convolutional-neural-network/jcr:content/mainParsys/band_copy_copy_14735_1026954091/mainParsys/columns_1606542234_c/2/image.adapt.full.high.jpg/1530247928116.jpg">mathworks</a></p>\n<p>You can see above image which exaclty describes working methodology of CNN extraction of a feature from the image of a car.</p>\n<h3>Understanding at Deeper Level</h3>\n<p>CNN is made up of layers. Each layer transforms one volume of activations to another through a differentiable function. CNN use mainly three type of layers which are responsible to extract deeper features from particular class of image: <strong>Convolutional Layer</strong>, <strong>Pooling Layer</strong>, and <strong>Fully-Connected Layer</strong></p>\n<p>Let’s take a closer look to functionalities of each layer:</p>\n<h4>Convolutional Layer</h4>\n<p>a Convolutional Layer does multiple <strong>Convolutional Operations</strong> on multiple channel of image i.e. depth. Each convolution operation has a kernel which coulb be matrix smaller than height and width of the original image. Each kernel have their specific task such as sharpening, blurring, edge detection, and many more</p>\n<p><img src="/cnn-layer-7220e04048d58962e709b997f84792ac.gif" alt="cnn-layer.gif">\nImage Source: <a href="http://machinelearninguru.com/computer_vision/basics/convolution/convolution_layer.html">machinelearninguru</a></p>\n<p>As shown in above figure, </p>\n<p><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">a^2 + b^2 = c^2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="strut" style="height:0.8141079999999999em;"></span><span class="strut bottom" style="height:0.897438em;vertical-align:-0.08333em;"></span><span class="base"><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathit">a</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:0.8141079999999999em;"><span style="top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height:2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mord rule" style="margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;"></span><span class="mbin">+</span><span class="mord rule" style="margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathit">b</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:0.8141079999999999em;"><span style="top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height:2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mord rule" style="margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mord rule" style="margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathit">c</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height:0.8141079999999999em;"><span style="top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height:2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>',fields:{tagSlugs:["/tags/deep-learning/","/tags/machine-learning/"]},frontmatter:{title:"That's not enough, We have to go deeper",tags:["deep learning","machine learning"],date:"2018-08-08T15:42:39.873Z",description:"“Life is really simple, but we insist on making it complicated.”  ― Confucius"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/posts/thats-not-enouigh-we-have-to-go-deeper/"}}}});
